#Genus set up

Pull clinical meta file

meta<-read.csv("Umichgan_09.02.2022_postmatch.csv", header=T,row.names=1)

OTU file from Quime2 using silva ref Pull shared file from Quitta

data.trim<-read.csv("cleanup_q2silva_genusL6.counts_postmatch.csv", header=T,row.names=1)
data.trim<-as.matrix(data.trim)

Introduce threhsolds Now to thresholds and remove OTUs below 0.1% of the population

data.tmp<-decostand(data.trim,"total")*100
neg1<-which(data.tmp<0.1)
data.trim[neg1]<-0
pos<-which(colSums(data.trim)>0)
data.good<-data.trim[,pos]
dim(data.good)
## [1] 1203  423
otu<-data.good

Taxonomy file load taxonomy matching file

data.taxonomy<-read.csv("cleanup_q2silva_genusL6.taxonomy.csv", header=T, row.names=1)

ok so we need to deal with missing data - small number could remove lets combine all data (meta + otu.bas), then remove missing rows form data set based on NA in $bfvcpp Then we can subset data based on cols numbers into an otu set again for ordination.

rownames now listed as a column

##                   Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)    
## samples.tert.fvc   2   5736  2867.8   7.244 0.000794 ***
## Residuals        487 192800   395.9                     
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
shapiro.test(fvc.Max_OTU) #NOT NORMAL 
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  fvc.Max_OTU
## W = 0.97325, p-value = 8.345e-08
kruskal.test(fvc.Max_OTU~samples.tert.fvc) #P=0.0006
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  fvc.Max_OTU by samples.tert.fvc
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 14.582, df = 2, p-value = 0.0006817
fvc.meta.otu$tertile<-as.factor(fvc.meta.otu$tertile)
pairwise.wilcox.test(fvc.Max_OTU, samples.tert.fvc, p.adjust.method = "BH")
## 
##  Pairwise comparisons using Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction 
## 
## data:  fvc.Max_OTU and samples.tert.fvc 
## 
##              high   intermediate
## intermediate 0.0023 -           
## low          0.0018 0.8100      
## 
## P value adjustment method: BH
data.1<-cbind(fvc.Max_OTU, fvc.meta.otu$tertile)   #bind data by column 
data.1<-as.data.frame(data.1)      #generate data frame 
colnames(data.1)[2]="fvc_tertile"  #rename col 2 in data as fvc_tertile
colnames(data.1)
## [1] "fvc.Max_OTU" "fvc_tertile"
data.1$fvc_tertile<-as.factor(data.1$fvc_tertile)
#write.csv(data.1, "CleanUp.bas.maxOTU.fvctertile.csv")

ok lets try minimal R tips to plot data=data.1 which is a data frame

data.1 %>%
  group_by(fvc_tertile) %>%
  summarize(mean=mean(fvc.Max_OTU), sd=sd(fvc.Max_OTU))
## # A tibble: 3 x 3
##   fvc_tertile  mean    sd
##   <fct>       <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 1            51.6  19.9
## 2 2            52.1  19.5
## 3 3            59.1  20.3
ggplot(data.1, aes(x=fvc_tertile, y=fvc.Max_OTU, color=fvc_tertile))+
  geom_boxplot(width=0.35)+
  geom_jitter(shape=19, size=2, width=0.15)+
  scale_color_manual(name=NULL,
                     values=c("red", "orange", "blue"),
                     breaks=c("1", "2", "3"),
                     labels=c("Low", "Intermediate", "High"))+
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c("1", "2", "3"),
                   labels=c("Low", "Intermediate", "High"))+
  labs(title="Relationship between Maximun OTU and FVc tertiles",
       x=NULL,
       y="Maximum OTU")+
  theme_classic()

aov.maxotu.tert<-aov(fvc.Max_OTU~samples.tert.fvc)
summary(aov.maxotu.tert)

##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  shannon.fvc
## W = 0.99263, p-value = 0.01633
kruskal.test(shannon.fvc~samples.tert.fvc)

##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  shannon.fvc by samples.tert.fvc

## data:  fvc.otu.norm.df$g001

#DLCO and Alpha diversity

shannon.dl<-diversity(dlco.otu, "shannon")

summary(aov.8)

data.6<-cbind(shannon.dl.df, dlco.meta.otu$tertile)

data.6<-as.data.frame(data.6)
colnames(data.6)
## [1] "shannon.dl"            "dlco.meta.otu$tertile"
colnames(data.6)[1]="shannon"
colnames(data.6)[2]="dlco_tertile"
colnames(data.6)
## [1] "shannon"      "dlco_tertile"
summary(data.6)
##     shannon        dlco_tertile
##  Min.   :0.1192   Min.   :1    
##  1st Qu.:1.0787   1st Qu.:1    
##  Median :1.5345   Median :2    
##  Mean   :1.5142   Mean   :2    
##  3rd Qu.:1.9399   3rd Qu.:3    
##  Max.   :3.0719   Max.   :3
data.6$dlco_tertile<-as.factor(data.6$dlco_tertile)
ggplot(data.6, aes(x=dlco_tertile, y=shannon, color=dlco_tertile))+
  geom_boxplot(width=0.35)+
  geom_jitter(shape=19, size=2, width=0.15)+
  scale_color_manual(name=NULL,
                     values=c("red", "orange", "blue"),
                     breaks=c("1", "2", "3"),
                     labels=c("Low", "Intermediate", "High"))+
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c("1", "2", "3"),
                   labels=c("Low", "Intermediate", "High"))+
  labs(title="Relationship between shannon and dlco tertile",
       x=NULL,
       y="Relative Abundance")+
  theme_classic()
